The paper deals with the task of cattle re-identification using deep CNNs and machine learning algorithms. This task involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning architectures and the comparison with standard machine learning algorithms suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The task of cattle re-identification also involves multi-view image analysis, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as it deals with the problem of identifying and retrieving specific cattle individuals from a large dataset.
